-- South African Stocks Advance For a Second Day, Led by Harmony, Gold Fields
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-10-05T16:23:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/south-african-benchmark-stock-index-gains-led-by-harmony-gold-gold-fields.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  rose for a second day, advancing 274.07, or 0.9
percent, to 29,569.04 by close at 5 p.m. in Johannesburg. The
following were among the most active stocks in the South African
market today.  Allied Electronics Corp. Ltd.  (ATN SJ) climbed 83 cents, or
3.1 percent, to 27.50 rand, its biggest gain since July 29. The
investment group with interests in communications equipment said
first-half profit jumped 21 percent to 294 million rand ($42
million).  Datacentrix Holdings Ltd.  (DCT SJ), the technology company
focusing on hardware, software and networking services, rose 15
cents, or 3.6 percent, to 4.35 rand, its biggest climb since
June 18. The company said first half revenue rose 22 percent.  Harmony Gold Mining Company Ltd.  (HAR SJ), Africa’s third-
largest producer of the metal, rose 3.10 rand, or 4 percent, to
81.40 rand, its biggest gain since Sept. 14.  Gold Fields Ltd. 
(GFI SJ), Africa’s second-largest gold producer, added 3.69
rand, or 3.5 percent, to 109.79 rand. Gold for immediate
delivery gained as much as 1.9 percent to a record $1,339.0 an
ounce.  Esorfranki Ltd.  (ESR SJ) fell 21 cents, or 9.8 percent, to
1.94 rand, its biggest fall since Feb. 27, 2009. The provider of
engineering services said first-half headline earnings a share
fell as much as 95 percent.  Zeder Investments Ltd.  (ZED SJ) advanced 1 cent, or 0.5
percent, to 2.21 rand. The company, which invests in agriculture
businesses, said profit rose 22 percent to 96.5 million rand in
the six months through Aug. 31 from a year earlier.  To contact the reporters on this story:
